==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnificence
<hw>Mag*nif"i*cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>magnificence</ets>, L. <ets>magnificentia</ets>. See
<er>Magnific</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of doing what is magnificent; the
state or quality of being magnificent.</def> <au>Acts xix. 27.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Then cometh <xex>magnificence</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, for the heaven's wide circuit, let it speak⟦br⟧
The Maker's high <qex>magnificence</qex>, who built⟦br⟧
so spacious.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The noblest monuments of Roman <qex>magnificence.</qex></q>
<rj><qau>Eustace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnificent</ent>⟦br⟧
